<paragraph id="8BB6368C92407722FF43FF4EFDBCBD4B" blockId="16.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">
C 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FF2EFF4EFE27BCF3" bold="true" box="[208,438,158,184]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">onservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FE48FF4EFD2BBCF3" box="[438,698,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92407722FE2DFF4EFD2BBCF3" box="[467,698,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="igrapiuna">Bertolonia igrapiuna</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has an EOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992407722FC96FF4EFC3FBCF0" box="[872,942,158,187]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" unit="km" value="28.0">28 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992407722FBB6FF4EFB01BCF0" box="[1096,1168,158,187]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" unit="km" value="16.0">16 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR), following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92407722FD72FF12FCB7BC97" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[652,806,194,220]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. This species has been found exclusively in “Parque Nacional Serra das Lontras”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB6368C92407722FF43FEDAFB77BE0F" blockId="16.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FF43FEDAFE98BD6F" bold="true" box="[189,265,266,292]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92407722FED8FEDAFD84BD6F" box="[294,533,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="igrapiuna">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FED8FEDAFD84BD6F" box="[294,533,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">Bertolonia igrapiuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92407722FD3CFEDAFC97BD6F" box="[706,774,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation id="13322A0992407722FB67FEDAFB7FBD6F" box="[1177,1262,266,292]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[341,1239,654,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-255@5.[340,1247,641,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A. Bertolonia alternifolia. B. Bertolonia angustipetala. C. Bertolonia bullata. D. Bertolonia carmoi. E. Bertolonia cuspidata. F. Bertolonia hirsutissima. G. Bertolonia igrapiuna. H. Bertolonia kollmannii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597686/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992407722FB31FEDAFB7FBD6F" box="[1231,1262,266,292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). Collected with flowers from November to March, and fruits from December to June. The species is characterized by the branches, petioles and leaf blades only glandulose-punctate, by the elliptic or ovate leaf blades with shortly attenuate, obtuse or occasionally asymmetric base, and anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92407722FB54FEA7FDB0BDFF" authority="(Bonpland 1823: 144) De Candolle (1828: 113)" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityPageNumber="113" authorityYear="1828" baseAuthorityName="Bonpland" baseAuthorityPageNumber="144" baseAuthorityYear="1823" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leuzeana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FB54FEA7FABFBDDB" box="[1194,1326,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">B. leuzeana</emphasis>
(Bonpland 1823: 144) 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92407722FEF7FE4BFDB0BDFF" author="De Candolle, A. P." box="[265,545,410,437]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" pagination="99 - 202" refId="ref19166" refString="De Candolle, A. P. (1828) Melastomataceae. In: Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis 3. Sumptibus Sociorum Treuttel &amp; Wurtz, Paris, pp. 99 - 202." type="book chapter" year="1828">De Candolle (1828: 113)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92407722FD14FE4AFC1EBDFF" box="[746,911,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
. Both have flat, ovate or elliptic leaf blades with non-cordate bases (attenuate or obtuse in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92407722FD9AFE6FFD62BD93" box="[612,755,447,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="igrapiuna">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FD9AFE6FFD62BD93" box="[612,755,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">B. igrapiuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, acute in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92407722FC98FE6FFC7ABD93" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" baseAuthorityName="Bonpland" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[870,1003,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leuzeana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FC98FE6FFC7ABD93" box="[870,1003,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">B. leuzeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and sparse ciliate margins. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92407722FACAFE6EFF67BDB7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="igrapiuna">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FACAFE6EFF67BDB7" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">Bertolonia igrapiuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the leaf blades only glandulose-punctate (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FCB5FE33FCF3BDB7" box="[843,866,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">vs</emphasis>
. the abaxial surface also sparsely glandulose-pilose in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92407722FF5BFDD7FEB8BE6B" authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" baseAuthorityName="Bonpland" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[165,297,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leuzeana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FF5BFDD7FEB8BE6B" box="[165,297,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">B. leuzeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), petals with apiculate apex ending in a glandular head (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FC56FDD7FC2EBE6B" box="[936,959,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">vs</emphasis>
. petals not apiculate) and anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FE55FDFBFE53BE0F" box="[427,450,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">vs</emphasis>
. introrse pore). For more details see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92407722FCA1FDFAFBC6BE0F" author="Bisewski, G. C. A. &amp; Bacci, L. &amp; Amorim, A. M. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[863,1111,554,580]" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" pagination="563 - 574" refId="ref18940" refString="Bisewski, G. C. A., Bacci, L. F, Amorim, A. M. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2020) Novelties in Bertolonia (Melastomataceae) from northeastern Brazil. Brazilian Journal of Botany 43 (3): 563 - 574. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 40415 - 020 - 00630 - 7" type="journal article" year="2020">
Bisewski 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92407722FC33FDFBFB94BE0F" box="[973,1029,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="169">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation id="C68B033792407722FB72FDFAFB71BE0F" box="[1164,1248,554,580]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="16" pageNumber="169" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
